Even that is a bit suspect, because ownership may well remain with you even after the call, so it's not really removed.For example, this is perfectly valid C++, and it is guaranteed to have no issue:  std::string abc = "abc";
  std::move(abc); //doesn't remove ownership or do anything really
  std::print(abc); //guaranteed to print "abc"

comments.content_cn:
即便如此，这一点也值得怀疑，因为即使在调用之后所有权很可能仍属于你，所以它并没有真正被移除。例如，这段C++代码完全有效，并且保证不会有问题：std::string abc = "abc";
std::move(abc); //并不会移除所有权或实际执行任何操作
std::print(abc); //保证会打印出"abc"

